Ikechukwu Onwuka

Bio

Ikechukwu (Ike) Onwuka is a PhD Candidate at @FIUEnvironment who studies nutrient, sediment and water interactions in the canals of South Florida and America’s Everglades. I use surrogate measurements to develop high frequency continuous water quality measurements and data science tools to detect patterns in aquatic systems to make inferences and predictions for water resource management. I am interested in using data science to connect water, aquatic sciences, climate change and food security to environmental sustainability. I am looking to collaborate with industry, academia, intergovernmental and global organizations, such as the United Nations.

Education

Florida International University | Miami, FL

Ph.D. in Earth Systems Science | Expected August 2022

Florida International University | Miami, FL

M.S. in Environmental Studies | August 2020

University of Ghana, Legon | Accra, Ghana

B.SC. in Oceanography | May 2013

Experience

PhD Candidate | Everglades Foundation Fellow | January 2021 - Present

PhD Student/Candidate | Graduate Teaching Assistant | August 2016 - December 2020
